#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
msgid "Starting the X Window System"
msgstr "Démarrer le système X Window"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"The X Window System is usually started as an <ulink url=\"&xsession;\">X "
"session</ulink> which is the combination of an X server and connecting X "
"clients.  For the normal desktop system, both of them are executed on a "
"workstation."
msgstr ""
"Le système X Window est habituellement démarré en tant que <ulink url="
"\"&xsession;\">session X</ulink> qui est la combinaison d'un serveur X et de "
"la connexions de clients X. Pour le système de bureau normal, les deux "
"tournent sur la station de travail."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"&xsession;\">X session</ulink> is started by the following."
msgstr ""
"La <ulink url=\"&xsession;\">session X</ulink> peut être démarrée par&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "<literal>startx</literal> command started from the command line"
msgstr ""
"la commande <literal>startx</literal> lancée depuis la ligne de "
"commande&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"One of the <ulink url=\"&xdisplaymanager;\">X display manager</ulink> daemon "
"programs <literal>*dm</literal> started from the end of the start up script "
"in \"<literal>/etc/rc?.d/</literal>\" (\"<literal>?</literal>\" "
"corresponding to the runlevel) directory"
msgstr ""
"un des programmes démons <ulink url=\"&xdisplaymanager;\">gestionnaire de "
"l’affichage X</ulink> <literal>*dm</literal> démarré à la fin du script de "
"démarrage du répertoire «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/rc?.d/</literal>&nbsp;» («&nbsp;"
"<literal>?</literal>&nbsp;» correspond au niveau de fonctionnement)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"The start up script for the display manager daemons checks the content of "
"the \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</literal>\" file before "
"actually executing themselves.  This ensures to have only one <ulink url="
"\"&xdisplaymanager;\">X display manager</ulink> daemon program activated."
msgstr ""
"Le script de démarrage des démons de gestion d'affichage examine d'abord le "
"contenu du fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</"
"literal>&nbsp;» avant leur exécution proprement dite. Cela permet de "
"s'assurer qu'un seul programme démon <ulink url=\"&xdisplaymanager;\">X "
"display manager</ulink> est activé."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"See <xref linkend=\"_specific_locale_only_under_x_window\"/> for initial "
"environment variables of the X display manager."
msgstr ""
"Consultez <xref linkend=\"_specific_locale_only_under_x_window\"/> pour les "
"variables d'environnement initiales du gestionnaire d'affichage X."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"Essentially, all these programs execute the \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>\" script.  Then the \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\" script "
"performs <citerefentry><refentrytitle>run-parts</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> like action to execute scripts in the \"<literal>/"
"etc/X11/Xsession.d/</literal>\" directory. This is essentially an execution "
"of a first program which is found in the following order with the "
"<literal>exec</literal> builtin command."
msgstr ""
"Essentiellement, tous ces programmes exécutent le script «&nbsp;<literal>/"
"etc/X11/Xsession</literal>&nbsp;\". Ensuite,, le script «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/"
"X11/Xsession</literal>&nbsp;» effectue une action de type "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>run-parts</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> pour exécuter les scripts se trouvant dans le "
"répertoire «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.d/</literal>&nbsp;». Le premier "
"programme trouve, dans l’ordre suivant, est exécuté à l’aide de la commande "
"«&nbsp;<literal>exec</literal>&nbsp;» intégrée&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The script specified as the argument of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>\" by the X display manager, if it is defined."
msgstr ""
"le script indiqué comme paramètre de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</"
"literal>&nbsp;» par le gestionnaire d'affichage X, s'il est défini&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>~/.xsession</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.Xsession</literal>\" "
"script, if it is defined."
msgstr ""
"le script «&nbsp;<literal>~/.xsession</literal>&nbsp;» ou «&nbsp;<literal>~/."
"Xsession</literal>&nbsp;», s'il est défini&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-session-manager</literal>\" command, if it is "
"defined."
msgstr ""
"la commande «&nbsp;<literal>/usr/bin/x-session-manager</literal>&nbsp;», si "
"elle est définie&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-window-manager</literal>\" command, if it is "
"defined."
msgstr ""
"la commande «&nbsp;<literal>/usr/bin/x-window-manager</literal>&nbsp;», si "
"elle est définie&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>/usr/bin/x-terminal-emulator</literal>\" command, if it is "
"defined."
msgstr ""
"la commande «&nbsp;<literal>/usr/bin/x-terminal-emulator</literal>&nbsp;», "
"si elle est définie."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"This process is affected by the content of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession."
"options</literal>\".  The exact programs to which these \"<literal>/usr/bin/"
"x-*</literal>\" commands point, are determined by the Debian alternative "
"system and changed by \"<literal>update-alternatives --config x-session-"
"manager</literal>\", etc."
msgstr ""
"Ce processus est affecté par le contenu de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession."
"options</literal>&nbsp;». Les programmes exacts vers lesquelles pointent les "
"commandes «&nbsp;<literal>/usr/bin/x-*</literal>&nbsp;» sont déterminés par "
"le système d'alternatives de Debian et sont modifiés par «&nbsp;"
"<literal>update-alternatives --config x-session-manager</literal>&nbsp;», "
"etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Starting X session with gdm3"
msgstr "Démarrer une session X avec gdm3"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdm3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> lets you select the session type (or desktop environment: "
"<xref linkend=\"_setting_up_desktop_environment\"/>), and language (or "
"locale: <xref linkend=\"_the_locale\"/>) of the X session from its menu.  It "
"keeps the selected default value in \"<literal>~/.dmrc</literal>\" as the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdm3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> vous permet de sélectionner le type de session (ou "
"d'environnement de bureau&nbsp;: <xref linkend="
"\"_setting_up_desktop_environment\"/>), la langue (ou «&nbsp;"
"locale&nbsp;»&nbsp;: <xref linkend=\"_the_locale\"/>) de la session X depuis "
"son menu. Il conserve les valeurs par défaut dans «&nbsp;<literal>~/.dmrc</"
"literal>&nbsp;» sous la forme suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[Desktop]\n"
"Session=default\n"
"Language=ja_JP.UTF-8"
msgstr ""
"[Desktop]\n"
"Session=default\n"
"Language=fr_FR.UTF-8"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Customizing the X session (classic method)"
msgstr "Personnaliser la session X session (méthode classique)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"On a system where \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.options</literal>\" contains "
"a line \"<literal>allow-user-xsession</literal>\" without preceding "
"\"<literal>#</literal>\" characters, any user who defines \"<literal>~/."
"xsession</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.Xsession</literal>\" is able to "
"customize the action of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\" by "
"completely overriding the system code. The last command in the \"<literal>~/."
"xsession</literal>\" file should use form of \"<literal>exec some-window/"
"session-manager</literal>\" to start your favorite X window/session managers."
msgstr ""
"Sur un système où «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession.options</literal>&nbsp;» "
"contient une ligne «&nbsp;<literal>allow-user-xsession</literal> sans "
"caractère «&nbsp;<literal>#</literal>&nbsp;» la précédant, tout utilisateur "
"qui définit «&nbsp;<literal>~/.xsession</literal>&nbsp;» ou «&nbsp;"
"<literal>~/.Xsession</literal>&nbsp;» peut personnaliser l’action de «&nbsp;"
"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>&nbsp;» en passant outre le code du "
"système. La dernière commande dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>~/.xsession</"
"literal>&nbsp;» devrait toujours être de la forme «&nbsp;<literal>exec "
"un_gestionnaire_de_fenêtre_ou_de_session</literal>&nbsp;» afin de démarrer "
"vos gestionnaires favoris de fenêtres et de session X."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Customizing the X session (new method)"
msgstr "Personnaliser la session X session (nouvelle méthode)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Here are new methods to customize the X session without completely "
"overriding the system code as above."
msgstr ""
"Voici de nouvelles méthodes de configuration de la session X sans "
"complètement outrepasser le code système comme ci-dessus&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The display manager <literal>gdm3</literal> can select a specific session "
"and set it as the argument of \"<literal>/etc/X11/Xsession</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"le gestionnaire d'affichage <literal>gdm3</literal> peut sélectionner une "
"session particulière et la définir comme paramètre de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/"
"X11/Xsession</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>~/.xsessionrc</literal>\" file is executed as a part of start "
"up process. (desktop independent)"
msgstr ""
"le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>~/.xsessionrc</literal>&nbsp;» est exécuté dans "
"le cadre du processus de démarrage (indépendant du bureau)&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>~/.gnomerc</literal>\" file is executed as a part of start up "
"process. (GNOME desktop only)"
msgstr ""
"le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>~/.gnomerc</literal>&nbsp;» est exécuté dans le "
"cadre du processus de démarrage (bureau GNOME uniquement)&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The GUI program based session management software may use the \"<literal>~/."
"gnome2/session</literal>\" file etc."
msgstr ""
"le logiciel de gestion de session basé sur une interface graphique peut "
"utiliser le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>~/.gnome2/session</literal>&nbsp;», etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Connecting a remote X client via SSH"
msgstr "Connecter un client X distant par SSH"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The use of \"<literal>ssh -X</literal>\" enables a secure connection from a "
"local X server to a remote application server."
msgstr ""
"L’utilisation de «&nbsp;<literal>ssh -X</literal>&nbsp;» active une "
"connexion sécurisée entre le serveur X local et une application sur un "
"serveur distant."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Set \"<literal>X11Forwarding</literal>\" entries to \"<literal>yes</literal>"
"\" in \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" of the remote host, if you "
"want to avoid \"<literal>-X</literal>\" command-line option."
msgstr ""
"Si vous désirez éviter l’option «&nbsp;<literal>-X</literal>&nbsp;» de la "
"ligne de commandes, définissez à «&nbsp;<literal>yes</literal>&nbsp;» les "
"entrées «&nbsp;<literal>X11Forwarding</literal>&nbsp;» de «&nbsp;<literal>/"
"etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>&nbsp;» sur la machine distante, "

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Start the X server on the local host."
msgstr "Démarrez le serveur X sur la station locale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Open an <literal>xterm</literal> in the local host."
msgstr "Ouvrez un <literal>xterm</literal> sur la machine locale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Run <citerefentry><refentrytitle>ssh</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> to establish a connection with the remote site as "
"the following."
msgstr ""
"Lancez <citerefentry><refentrytitle>ssh</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> pour établir une connexion avec un site distant "
"comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"localname @ localhost $ ssh -q -X loginname@remotehost.domain\n"
"Password:"
msgstr ""
"utilisateur_local @ localhost $ ssh -q -X -l nom_utilisateur@machine_distante.domaine\n"
"Password:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Run an X application command, e.g. \"<literal>gimp</literal>\", on the "
"remote site as the following."
msgstr ""
"Lancez comme suit une application X, par exemple «&nbsp;<literal>gimp</"
"literal>&nbsp;» sur le site distant&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "loginname @ remotehost $ gimp &amp;"
msgstr "nom_utilisateur @ machine_distante $ gimp &amp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"This method can display the output from a remote X client as if it were "
"locally connected through a local UNIX domain socket."
msgstr ""
"Cette méthode permet l’affichage du client X distant comme s'il était "
"connecté par une socket UNIX locale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Secure X terminal via the Internet"
msgstr "Sécuriser le terminal X au travers d'Internet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Secure X terminal via the Internet, which displays remotely run entire X "
"desktop environment, can easily achieved by using specialized package such "
"as <literal>ldm</literal>. Your local machine becomes a secure thin client "
"to the remote application server connected via SSH."
msgstr ""
"La sécurisation du terminal X par Internet, qui affiche localement un "
"environnement de bureau qui tourne entièrement de manière distante, peut "
"être facilement réalisée en utilisant des paquets spécialisés tels que "
"<literal>ldm</literal>. Votre machine locale devient un client léger "
"sécurisé du serveur d'applications connecté par SSH."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
msgid "Fonts in the X Window"
msgstr "Polices dans X Window"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfigca;\">Fontconfig 2.0</ulink> was created to provide "
"a distribution independent library for configuring and customizing font "
"access in 2002.  Debian after <literal>squeeze</literal> uses <ulink url="
"\"&fontconfigca;\">Fontconfig 2.0</ulink> for its font configuration."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfigca;\">Fontconfig 2.0</ulink> a été créé en 2002 pour "
"fournir une bibliothèque indépendante de la distribution destinée à "
"configurer et personnaliser l’accès aux polices. Debian, pour les versions "
"ultérieures à <literal>squeeze</literal> utilise <ulink url=\"&fontconfigca;"
"\">Fontconfig 2.0</ulink> pour la configuration de ses polices."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid "Font supports on X Window System can be summarized as follows."
msgstr ""
"La prise en compte des polices dans le système X Window peut être résumée "
"comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Legacy X server side font support system"
msgstr "Ancien système de gestion des polices côté serveur X"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The original core X11 font system provides backward compatibility for older "
"version of X client applications."
msgstr ""
"Le système de polices de base d'origine de X11 fournit une "
"rétrocompatibilité avec les anciennes versions des applications X clientes."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "The original core X11 fonts are installed on the X server."
msgstr "Les polices de base d'origine de X11 sont installées sur le serveur X."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Modern X client side font support system"
msgstr "Système de prise en charge moderne des polices côté client X"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"Modern X system supports all fonts listed below (<xref linkend=\"_basic_fonts"
"\"/>, <xref linkend=\"_additional_fonts\"/>, and <xref linkend=\"_cjk_fonts"
"\"/>) with advanced features such as anti-aliasing."
msgstr ""
"Les systèmes X modernes prennent en charge toutes les polices dont la liste "
"figure ci-dessous (<xref linkend=\"_basic_fonts\"/>, <xref linkend="
"\"_additional_fonts\"/> et <xref linkend=\"_cjk_fonts\"/>) avec des "
"fonctionnalités avancées telles que l’anti-crénelage."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&xft;\">Xft</ulink> 2.0 connects modern X applications such as "
"ones from <ulink url=\"&gnome;\">GNOME</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&kde;\">KDE</"
"ulink>, and <ulink url=\"&openofficeorg;\">OpenOffice.org</ulink> with "
"<ulink url=\"&freetype;\">FreeType</ulink> 2.0 library."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&xft;\">Xft</ulink> 2.0 connecte les applications X modernes "
"telles que celles de <ulink url=\"&gnome;\">GNOME</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&kde;"
"\">KDE</ulink> et <ulink url=\"&openofficeorg;\">OpenOffice.org</ulink> avec "
"la bibliothèque <ulink url=\"&freetype;\">FreeType</ulink> 2.0"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&freetype;\">FreeType</ulink> 2.0 provides font rasterization "
"library."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&freetype;\">FreeType</ulink> 2.0 fournit une bibliothèque de "
"tramage des polices."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfig;\">Fontconfig</ulink> provides resolution of the "
"font specification for <ulink url=\"&xft;\">Xft</ulink> 2.0.  See "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>fonts.conf</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> for its configuration."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfig;\">Fontconfig</ulink> fournit une résolution de la "
"spécification des polices pour <ulink url=\"&xft;\">Xft</ulink> 2.0. "
"Consultez <citerefentry><refentrytitle>fonts.conf</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> pour sa configuration."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"All modern X applications using <ulink url=\"&xft;\">Xft</ulink> 2.0 can "
"talk to modern X server using the <ulink url=\"&xrenderingextension;\">X "
"Rendering Extension</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les applications X modernes qui utilisent <ulink url=\"&xft;\">Xft</"
"ulink> 2.0 peuvent dialoguer avec un serveur X moderne en utilisant l’<ulink "
"url=\"&xrenderingextension;\">extension de rendu X</ulink> («&nbsp;X "
"Rendering Extension&nbsp;»)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"&xrenderingextension;\">X Rendering Extension</ulink> moves "
"font access and glyph image generation from the X server to the X client."
msgstr ""
"L’<ulink url=\"&xrenderingextension;\">extension de rendu X</ulink> déplace "
"l’accès aux polices et la génération des images de glyphes du serveur vers "
"le client X."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><table><title>
msgid "Table of packages to support X Window font systems"
msgstr "Table de paquets prenant en charge les systèmes de polices de X Window"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "X Window System font utility programs"
msgstr "Programmes utilitaires des polices du système X Window"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid ""
"Xft, a library that connects X applications with the FreeType font "
"rasterization library"
msgstr ""
"Xft, bibliothèque permettant de connecter des applications X avec la "
"bibliothèque de tramage des polices FreeType"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&freetype;\">FreeType</ulink> 2.0 font rasterization library"
msgstr ""
"Bibliothèque de tramage des polices <ulink url=\"&freetype;\">FreeType</"
"ulink> 2.0"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfig;\">Fontconfig</ulink>, a generic font configuration "
"library — support binaries"
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfig;\">Fontconfig</ulink>, bibliothèque générique de "
"configuration des polices  — binaires de gestion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfig;\">Fontconfig</ulink>, a generic font configuration "
"library — configuration data"
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&fontconfig;\">Fontconfig</ulink>, bibliothèque générique de "
"configuration des polices — données de configuration"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid "You can check font configuration information by the following."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez vérifier les informations de configuration des polices comme "
"suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>xset q</literal>\" for core X11 font path"
msgstr ""
"«&nbsp;<literal>xset q</literal>&nbsp;» pour le chemin des police X11 de base"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>fc-match</literal>\" for fontconfig font default"
msgstr ""
"«&nbsp;<literal>fc-match</literal>&nbsp;» pour la police par défaut de "
"fontconfig"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>fc-list</literal>\" for available fontconfig fonts"
msgstr ""
"«&nbsp;<literal>fc-list</literal>&nbsp;» pour les polices disponibles de "
"fontconfig"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"\"<ulink url=\"&thepenguinandunicode;\">The Penguin and Unicode</ulink>\" is "
"a good overview of modern X Window System. Other documentations at <ulink "
"url=\"&httpunifontorg;\">http://unifont.org/</ulink> should provide good "
"information on Unicode fonts, Unicode-enabled software, "
"internationalization, and Unicode usability issues on <ulink url="
"\"&freelibreopensourcefloss;\">free/libre/open source (FLOSS)</ulink> "
"operating systems."
msgstr ""
"«&nbsp;<ulink url=\"&thepenguinandunicode;\">Unicode et le Pingouin</"
"ulink>&nbsp;» («&nbsp;The Penguin and Unicode&nbsp;») est un bon aperçu du "
"système X Window moderne. D'autres documentations se trouvant à <ulink url="
"\"&httpunifontorg;\">http://unifont.org/</ulink> devraient fournir de bonnes "
"informations sur les polices Unicode, les logiciels fonctionnant avec "
"Unicode, l’internationalisation et les problèmes d'utilisation d'Unicode sur "
"les systèmes d'exploitation<ulink url=\"&freelibreopensourcefloss;\">free/"
"libre/open source (FLOSS)</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Basic fonts"
msgstr "Polices de base"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"There are 2 major types of <ulink url=\"&computerfonts;\">computer fonts</"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Il y a deux types principaux de <ulink url=\"&computerfonts;\">polices de "
"caractères pour ordinateurs</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Bitmap fonts (good for low resolution rasterization)"
msgstr ""
"Polices par champs de bits («&nbsp;bitmap&nbsp;») (bonnes pour le tramage en "
"faible résolution)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Outline/stroke fonts (good for high resolution rasterization)"
msgstr ""
"Polices par traits/contours (bonnes pour le tramage en haute résolution)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"While scaling of bitmap fonts causes jugged image, scaling of outline/stroke "
"fonts produces smooth image."
msgstr ""
"Alors que le redimensionnement des polices bitmap donne des images hachées, "
"le redimensionnement des polices par traits et contours donne des images "
"lisses."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Bitmap fonts on the Debian system are usually provided by compressed <ulink "
"url=\"&xbbpcfbitmapfontfiles;\">X11 pcf bitmap font files</ulink> having "
"their file extension \"<literal>.pcf.gz</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Les polices bitmap sur le système Debian sont habituellement fournie sous "
"forme de <ulink url=\"&xbbpcfbitmapfontfiles;\">fichiers de police X11 pcf "
"bitmap</ulink> compressés ayant l’extension de nom de fichier «&nbsp;"
"<literal>.pcf.gz</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Outline fonts on the Debian system are provided by the following."
msgstr ""
"Les polices de type contour sur les système Debian sont fournies de la "
"manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&postscript;\">PostScript</ulink> Type 1 font files having "
"their file extension \"<literal>.pfb</literal>\" (binary font file) and "
"\"<literal>.afm</literal>\" (font metrics file)."
msgstr ""
"Fichiers de polices <ulink url=\"&postscript;\">PostScript</ulink> Type 1 "
"avec une extension de nom de fichier «&nbsp;<literal>.pfb</"
"literal>&nbsp;» (fichier binaire de police) et «&nbsp;<literal>.afm</"
"literal>&nbsp;» (fichier de métrique de la police)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&truetype;\">TrueType</ulink> (or <ulink url=\"&opentype;"
"\">OpenType</ulink>) font files usually having their file extension "
"\"<literal>.ttf</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Fichiers de polices <ulink url=\"&truetype;\">TrueType</ulink> (ou <ulink "
"url=\"&opentype;\">OpenType</ulink>) ayant habituellement l’extension «&nbsp;"
"<literal>.ttf</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"&opentype;\">OpenType</ulink> is intended to supersede both "
"<ulink url=\"&truetype;\">TrueType</ulink> and <ulink url=\"&postscript;"
"\">PostScript</ulink> Type 1."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"&opentype;\">OpenType</ulink> est prévu pour se substituer à la "
"fois à <ulink url=\"&truetype;\">TrueType</ulink> et <ulink url="
"\"&postscript;\">PostScript</ulink> Type 1."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
msgid ""
"Table of corresponding <ulink url=\"&postscript;\">PostScript</ulink> Type 1 "
