msgstr ""
"Bien que <citerefentry><refentrytitle>parted</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> prétend pouvoir créer et redimensionner aussi les "
"systèmes de fichiers, il est plus sûr de toucher à ces choses-là en "
"utilisant des outils spécialisés et bien maintenus tels que "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> (<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.msdos</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>, "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.ext2</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry>, <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.ext3</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>, …) et "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>resize2fs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"In order to switch between <ulink url=\"&gpt;\">GPT</ulink> and <ulink url="
"\"&mbr;\">MBR</ulink>, you need to erase first few blocks of disk contents "
"directly (see <xref linkend=\"_clearing_file_contents\"/>) and use "
"\"<literal>parted /dev/sdx mklabel gpt</literal>\" or \"<literal>parted /dev/"
"sdx mklabel msdos</literal>\" to set it.  Please note \"<literal>msdos</"
"literal>\" is use here for <ulink url=\"&mbr;\">MBR</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"De manière à passer de <ulink url=\"&gpt;\">GPT</ulink> à <ulink url=\"&mbr;"
"\">MBR</ulink>, il vous fait d'abord effacer les premier blocs du disque "
"directement (consultez <xref linkend=\"_clearing_file_contents\"/>) et "
"utiliser «&nbsp;<literal>parted /dev/sdx mklabel gpt</literal>&nbsp;» ou "
"«&nbsp;<literal>parted /dev/sdx mklabel msdos</literal>&nbsp;» afin de le "
"mettre en place. Vous remarquerez que «&nbsp;<literal>msdos</literal>&nbsp;» "
"est utilisé ici pour <ulink url=\"&mbr;\">MBR</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Accessing partition using UUID"
msgstr "Accès à une partition en utilisant l’UUID"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Although reconfiguration of your partition or activation order of removable "
"storage media may yield different names for partitions, you can access them "
"consistently. This is also helpful if you have multiple disks and your BIOS "
"doesn't give them consistent device names."
msgstr ""
"Bien que le reconfiguration de votre partition ou l’ordre d'activation des "
"supports d'enregistrement amovibles puisse conduire à des noms de partitions "
"différents, vous pouvez y accéder de manière homogène. Cela vous aidera "
"aussi si vous avez plusieurs disques et que votre BIOS ne leur donne pas "
"toujours le même nom de périphérique."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> with \"<literal>-U</literal>\" option can mount a block device "
"using <ulink url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink>, instead of using its file name "
"such as \"<literal>/dev/sda3</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> avec l’option «&nbsp;<literal>-U</literal>&nbsp;» peut monter "
"un périphérique en mode bloc en utilisant l’<ulink url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</"
"ulink> plutôt que son nom de fichier de périphérique comme «&nbsp;<literal>/"
"dev/sda3</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\" (see <citerefentry><refentrytitle>fstab</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry>) can use <ulink url="
"\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"«&nbsp;<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>&nbsp;» (consultez "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>fstab</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry>) peut utiliser l’<ulink url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"Boot loaders (<xref linkend=\"_stage_2_the_boot_loader\"/>) may use <ulink "
"url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink> too."
msgstr ""
"Les chargeurs initiaux (<xref linkend=\"_stage_2_the_boot_loader\"/>) "
"peuvent aussi utiliser <ulink url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You can probe <ulink url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink> of a block special device "
"with <citerefentry><refentrytitle>blkid</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry>."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez tester l’<ulink url=\"&uuid;\">UUID</ulink> d'un périphérique "
"spécial en mode bloc avec <citerefentry><refentrytitle>blkid</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"Device nodes of devices such as removable storage media can be made static "
"by using <ulink url=\"&udevrules;\">udev rules</ulink>, if needed.  See "
"<xref linkend=\"_the_udev_system\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Les nœuds de périphériques comme les supports d'enregistrement amovibles "
"peuvent être rendus statiques en utilisant, si besoin, des <ulink url="
"\"&udevrules;\">règles udev</ulink>. Consultez <xref linkend="
"\"_the_udev_system\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Filesystem configuration"
msgstr "Configuration de systèmes de fichiers"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"For <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> filesystem, the <literal>e2fsprogs</"
"literal> package provides the following."
msgstr ""
"Pour le système de fichiers <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink>, le paquet "
"<literal>e2fsprogs</literal> fournit les éléments suivants&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.ext3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> to create new <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> "
"filesystem"
msgstr ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.ext3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> pour créer un nouveau système de fichiers <ulink "
"url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>fsck.ext3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> to check and to repair existing <ulink url=\"&extd;"
"\">ext3</ulink> filesystem"
msgstr ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>fsck.ext3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> pour vérifier et réparer un système de fichiers "
"<ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> existant"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>tune2fs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> to configure superblock of <ulink url=\"&extd;"
"\">ext3</ulink> filesystem"
msgstr ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>tune2fs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> pour configurer le superbloc d'un système de "
"fichiers <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> and <citerefentry><refentrytitle>fsck</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry> commands are provided "
"by the <literal>e2fsprogs</literal> package as front-ends to various "
"filesystem dependent programs (<literal>mkfs.fstype</literal> and "
"<literal>fsck.fstype</literal>). For <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> "
"filesystem, they are <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.ext3</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry> and "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>fsck.ext3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> (they are hardlinked to "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mke2fs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> and <citerefentry><refentrytitle>e2fsck</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>)."
msgstr ""
"Les commandes <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> et <citerefentry><refentrytitle>fsck</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry> font partie du paquet "
"<literal>e2fsprogs</literal> en tant que frontal à de nombreux programmes "
"dépendant du système de fichiers (<literal>mkfs.fstype</literal> "
"et<literal>fsck.fstype</literal>). Pour le système de fichiers <ulink url="
"\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink>, il y a <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mkfs.ext3</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry> et "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>fsck.ext3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> (ils sont liés par un lien dur à "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>mke2fs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> et<citerefentry><refentrytitle>e2fsck</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>)."

