msgid ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>cvs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry>"
msgstr ""
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>cvs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>/usr/share/doc/cvs/html-cvsclient</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/cvs/html-cvsclient</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>/usr/share/doc/cvs/html-info</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/cvs/html-info</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>/usr/share/doc/cvsbook</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/cvsbook</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "\"<literal>info cvs</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>info cvs</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Configuration of CVS repository"
msgstr "Configuration du dépôt CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The following configuration allows commits to the CVS repository only by a "
"member of the \"<literal>src</literal>\" group, and administration of CVS "
"only by a member of the \"<literal>staff</literal>\" group, thus reducing "
"the chance of shooting oneself."
msgstr ""
"La configuration suivante permet de ne faire des dépôts («&nbsp;"
"commit&nbsp;») vers le dépôt du CVS que par les membres du groupe «&nbsp;"
"<literal>src</literal>&nbsp;» et l’administration du CVS que par un membre "
"du groupe «&nbsp;<literal>staff</literal>&nbsp;», réduisant ainsi la chance "
"de se détruire soi-même."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /var/lib; umask 002; mkdir cvs\n"
"# export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project\n"
"# cd $CVSROOT\n"
"# chown root:src .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# cvs -d $CVSROOT init\n"
"# cd CVSROOT\n"
"# chown -R root:staff .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# touch val-tags\n"
"# chmod 664 history val-tags\n"
"# chown root:src history val-tags"
msgstr ""
"# cd /var/lib; umask 002; mkdir cvs\n"
"# export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/projet\n"
"# cd $CVSROOT\n"
"# chown root:src .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# cvs -d $CVSROOT init\n"
"# cd CVSROOT\n"
"# chown -R root:staff .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# touch val-tags\n"
"# chmod 664 history val-tags\n"
"# chown root:src history val-tags"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You may restrict creation of new project by changing the owner of \"<literal>"
"$CVSROOT</literal>\" directory to \"<literal>root:staff</literal>\" and its "
"permission to \"<literal>3775</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez restreindre la création d'un nouveau projet en modifiant le "
"propriétaire du répertoire «&nbsp;<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>&nbsp;» pour "
"«&nbsp;<literal>root:staff</literal>&nbsp;» et ses permissions à «&nbsp;"
"<literal>3775</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Local access to CVS"
msgstr "Accès local à CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The default CVS repository is pointed by \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\".  "
"The following sets up \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" for the local access."
msgstr ""
"La variable «&nbsp;<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>&nbsp;» pointe vers le dépôt "
"par défaut. Ce qui suit définit «&nbsp;<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>&nbsp;» "
"pour l’accès local&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project"
msgstr "$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Remote access to CVS with pserver"
msgstr "Accès distant à CVS avec pserver"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Many public CVS servers provide read-only remote access to them with account "
"name \"<literal>anonymous</literal>\" via pserver service.  For example, "
"Debian web site contents are maintained by <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;"
"\">webwml project</ulink> via CVS at Debian alioth service.  The following "
"sets up \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" for the remote access to this CVS "
"repository."
msgstr ""
"De nombreux serveurs CVS d'accès public fournissent un accès distant en "
"lecture avec le nom de compte «&nbsp;<literal>anonymous</literal>&nbsp;» par "
"l’intermédiaire du service pserver. Par exemple, le contenu du site web "
"Debian est maintenu par l’intermédiaire du <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;"
"\">projet webwml</ulink> sous le CVS du service alioth de Debian. Ce qui "
"suit permet de configurer «&nbsp;<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>&nbsp;» pour un "
"accès distant à ce dépôt CVS&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVSROOT=:pserver:anonymous@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvsroot/webwml\n"
"$ cvs login"
msgstr ""
"$ export CVSROOT=:pserver:anonymous@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvsroot/webwml\n"
"$ cvs login"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"Since pserver is prone to eavesdropping attack and insecure, write access is "
"usually disable by server administrators."
msgstr ""
"Comme pserver est sujet à des attaques d'espionnage et peu sûr, l’accès en "
"écriture est habituellement désactivé par les administrateurs du serveur."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Remote access to CVS with ssh"
msgstr "Accès distant à CVS avec ssh"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The following sets up \"<literal>$CVS_RSH</literal>\" and \"<literal>"
"$CVSROOT</literal>\" for the remote access to the CVS repository by <ulink "
"url=\"&webwmlproject;\">webwml project</ulink> with SSH."
msgstr ""
"Ce qui suit définit «&nbsp;<literal>$CVS_RSH</literal>&nbsp;» et »&nbsp;"
"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>&nbsp;» pour l’accès distant avec SSH au dépôt "
"CVS du <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;\">projet webwml</ulink>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVS_RSH=ssh\n"
"$ export CVSROOT=:ext:account@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvs/webwml"
msgstr ""
"$ export CVS_RSH=ssh\n"
"$ export CVSROOT=:ext:account@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvs/webwml"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"You can also use public key authentication for SSH which eliminates the "
"remote password prompt."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez aussi utiliser une clé publique d'authentification pour SSH, ce "
"qui élimine l’invite à distance pour l’entrée du mot de passe."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Importing a new source to CVS"
msgstr "Importer une nouvelle source dans CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create a new local source tree location at \"<literal>~/path/to/module1</"
"literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Créez un nouvel emplacement d'arborescence locale des sources dans «&nbsp;"
"<literal>~/chemin/vers/module1</literal>&nbsp;» par la commande "
"suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ mkdir -p ~/path/to/module1; cd ~/path/to/module1"
msgstr "$ mkdir -p ~/chemin/vers/module1; cd ~/chemin/vers/module1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Populate a new local source tree under \"<literal>~/path/to/module1</literal>"
"\" with files."
msgstr ""
"Mettez des fichiers dans la nouvelles arborescence locale de sources se "
"trouvant en «&nbsp;<literal>~/chemin/vers/module1</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Import it to CVS with the following parameters."
msgstr "Importez-les vers CVS avec les paramètres suivants&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Module name: \"<literal>module1</literal>\""
msgstr "Module name&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>module1</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"Vendor tag: \"<literal>Main-branch</literal>\" (tag for the entire branch)"
msgstr ""
"Vendor tag: «&nbsp;<literal>Branche-principale</literal>&nbsp;» (étiquette "
"pour toute la branche)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid ""
"Release tag: \"<literal>Release-initial</literal>\" (tag for a specific "
"release)"
msgstr ""
"Release tag: «&nbsp;<literal>Version-initiale</literal>&nbsp;» (étiquette "
"pour une version spécifique)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to/module1\n"
"$ cvs import -m \"Start module1\" module1 Main-branch Release-initial\n"
"$ rm -Rf . # optional"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/chemin/vers/module1\n"
"$ cvs import -m \"Start module1\" module1 Branche-principale Version-initiale\n"
"$ rm -Rf . # optionnel"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "File permissions in CVS repository"
msgstr "Permissions des fichiers du dépôt CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"CVS does not overwrite the current repository file but replaces it with "
"another one.  Thus, write permission to the repository directory is "
"critical.  For every new module for \"<literal>module1</literal>\" in "
"repository at \"<literal>/srv/cvs/project</literal>\", run the following to "
"ensure this condition if needed."
msgstr ""
"CVS n'écrase pas un fichier du dépôt actuel mais le remplace par un autre. "
"La permission en écriture vers le répertoire du dépôt est donc critique. "
"Lancez ce qui suit, pour chaque nouveau module de «&nbsp;<literal>module1</"
"literal>&nbsp;» dans le dépôt à «&nbsp;<literal>/srv/cvs/projet</"
"literal>&nbsp;», afin de vous assurer, si nécessaire, que cette condition "
"est remplie&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /srv/cvs/project\n"
"# chown -R root:src module1\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   module1\n"
"# chmod    2775     module1"
msgstr ""
"# cd /srv/cvs/projet\n"
"# chown -R root:src module1\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   module1\n"
"# chmod    2775     module1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Work flow of CVS"
msgstr "Flux de travail avec CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Here is an example of typical work flow using CVS."
msgstr "Voici un exemple de flux de travail typique utilisant CVS."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Check all available modules from CVS project pointed by \"<literal>$CVSROOT</"
"literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Vérifiez tous les modules disponibles du projet CVS pointé par «&nbsp;"
"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs rls\n"
"CVSROOT\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ cvs rls\n"
"CVSROOT\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Checkout \"<literal>module1</literal>\" to its default directory "
"\"<literal>./module1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Récupérez le «&nbsp;<literal>module1</literal>&nbsp;» depuis son répertoire "
"par défaut «&nbsp;<literal>./module1</literal>&nbsp;» de la manière "
"suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co module1\n"
"$ cd module1"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co module1\n"
"$ cd module1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Make changes to the content as needed."
msgstr "Effectuez les modifications de contenu au besoin."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Check changes by making \"<literal>diff -u [repository] [local]</literal>\" "
"equivalent by the following."
msgstr ""
"Vérifiez les modifications par un équivalent de «&nbsp;<literal>diff -u "
"[repository] [local]</literal>&nbsp;» de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs diff -u"
msgstr "$ cvs diff -u"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"You find that you broke some file \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" "
"severely but other files are fine."
msgstr ""
"Vous-vous apercevez que vous avez cassé sévèrement un fichier appelé «&nbsp;"
"<literal>fichier_à_restaurer</literal>&nbsp;» mais que les autres fichiers "
"sont corrects."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Overwrite \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" file with the clean copy from "
"CVS by the following."
msgstr ""
"Écrasez le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>fichier_à_restaurer</literal>&nbsp;» avec "
"une copie propre venant du CVS de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -C file_to_undo"
msgstr "$ cvs up -C fichier_à_restaurer"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Save the updated local source tree to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Enregistrez l’arborescence source locale vers le CVS comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"Describe change\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"Décrire les modifications\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create and add \"<literal>file_to_add</literal>\" file to CVS by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Créez et ajoutez le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>fichier_à_ajouter</"
"literal>&nbsp;» au CVS comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ vi file_to_add\n"
"$ cvs add file_to_add\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Added file_to_add\""
msgstr ""
"$ vi fichier_à_ajouter\n"
"$ cvs add fichier_à_ajouter\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Ajout de fichier_à_ajouter\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Merge the latest version from CVS by the following."
msgstr "Fusionnez la dernière version depuis le CVS comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Watch out for lines starting with \"<literal>C filename</literal>\" which "
"indicates conflicting changes."
msgstr ""
"Recherchez les lignes commençant par «&nbsp;<literal>C filename</"
"literal>&nbsp;» qui indiquent des modifications en conflit."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Look for unmodified code in \"<literal>.#filename.version</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Recherchez du code non modifié dans «&nbsp;<literal>.#nom_fichier.version</"
"literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Search for \"<literal>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</literal>\" and "
"\"<literal>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</literal>\" in files for conflicting "
"changes."
msgstr ""
"Recherchez «&nbsp;<literal>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</literal>&nbsp;» et "
"«&nbsp;<literal>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</literal>&nbsp;» dans les "
"fichiers qui indiquent des conflits de modifications."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Edit files to fix conflicts as needed."
msgstr "Au besoin, éditez les fichiers pour résoudre les conflits."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Add a release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez l’étiquette de version («&nbsp;release tag«&nbsp;») «&nbsp;"
"<literal>Version-1</literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs ci -m \"last commit for Release-1\"\n"
"$ cvs tag Release-1"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs ci -m \"dernière proposition pour Version-1\"\n"
"$ cvs tag Version-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Edit further."
msgstr "Poursuivez l’édition."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Remove the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Supprimez l’étiquette de version «&nbsp;<literal>Version-1</literal> &nbsp;» "
"comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs tag -d Release-1"
msgstr "$ cvs tag -d Version-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Check in changes to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Vérifiez les modifications du CVS comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"real last commit for Release-1\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"vraiment la dernière proposition pour Version-1\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Re-add the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" to updated CVS HEAD "
"of main by the following."
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez de nouveau, de la manière suivante, l’étiquette «&nbsp;"
"<literal>Version-1</literal>&nbsp;» à HEAD de «&nbsp;main&nbsp;» du CVS mis "
"à jour&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs tag Release-1"
msgstr "$ cvs tag Version-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create a branch with a sticky branch tag \"<literal>Release-initial-"
"bugfixes</literal>\" from the original version pointed by the tag "
"\"<literal>Release-initial</literal>\" and check it out to \"<literal>~/path/"
"to/old</literal>\" directory by the following."
msgstr ""
"Créez une branche avec une étiquette de branche «&nbsp;collante&nbsp;» "
"<literal>Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues</literal>&nbsp;» depuis la "
"version d'origine pointée par l’étiquette «&nbsp;<literal>Version-initiale</"
"literal>&nbsp;» et exportez-la vers le répertoire <literal>~/chemin/vers/"
"ancien</literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs rtag -b -r Release-initial Release-initial-bugfixes module1\n"
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co -r Release-initial-bugfixes -d old module1\n"
"$ cd old"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs rtag -b -r Version-initiale Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues module1\n"
"$ cd ~/chemin/vers\n"
"$ cvs co -r Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues -d ancien module1\n"
"$ cd ancien"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"Use \"<literal>-D 2005-12-20</literal>\" (<ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</"
"ulink> date format) instead of \"<literal>-r Release-initial</literal>\" to "
"specify particular date as the branch point."
msgstr ""
"Utilisez &nbsp;<literal>-D 2005-12-20</literal>&nbsp;» (format de date "
"<ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink>) plutôt que «&nbsp;<literal>-r "
"Version-initiale</literal>&nbsp;» pour indiquer une date particulière comme "
"point de branche."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Work on this local source tree having the sticky tag \"<literal>Release-"
"initial-bugfixes</literal>\" which is based on the original version."
msgstr ""
"Travaillez sur cette arborescence locale possédant l’étiquette «&nbsp;"
"collante&nbsp;» «&nbsp;<literal>Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues</"
"literal>&nbsp;» qui est basée sur la version d'origine."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Work on this branch by yourself … until someone else joins to this "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch."
msgstr ""
"Travaillez vous-même sur cette branche… jusqu'à ce que quelqu'un d'autre "
"rejoigne cette branche «&nbsp;<literal>Version-initiale-corrections-de-"
"bogues</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Sync with files modified by others on this branch while creating new "
"directories as needed by the following."
msgstr ""
"Synchronisez les fichiers modifiés par d'autres sur cette branche, en créant "
"de nouveaux répertoires si nécessaire, de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"checked into this branch\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"checked into this branch\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Update the local tree by HEAD of main while removing sticky tag (\"<literal>-"
"A</literal>\") and without keyword expansion (\"<literal>-kk</literal>\") by "
"the following."
msgstr ""
"Mettez à jour l’arborescence locale depuis HEAD de main en supprimant "
"l’étiquette collante («&nbsp;sticky tag&nbsp;») («&nbsp;<literal>-A</"
"literal>&nbsp;») et sans expansion de mots-clés («&nbsp;<literal>-kk</"
"literal>&nbsp;») comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d -kk -A"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d -kk -A"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Update the local tree (content = HEAD of main) by merging from the "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch and without keyword "
"expansion by the following."
msgstr ""
"Mettez à jour l’arborescence locale (contenu = HEAD de main) en fusionnant "
"depuis la branche «&nbsp;<literal>Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues</"
"literal>&nbsp;» et sans expansion des mots-clés en faisant ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d -kk -j Release-initial-bugfixes"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d -kk -j Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Fix conflicts with editor."
msgstr "Corrigez les conflits avec l’éditeur."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"merged Release-initial-bugfixes\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues fusionnée\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Make archive by the following."
msgstr "Réalisez une archive de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ mv old old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ tar -cvzf old-module1-bugfixes.tar.gz old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ rm -rf old-module1-bugfixes"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ mv ancien ancien-module1-corrections_bogues\n"
"$ tar -cvzf ancien-module1-corrections_bogues.tar.gz ancien-module1-corrections_bogues\n"
"$ rm -rf ancien-module1-corrections_bogues"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"\"<literal>cvs up</literal>\" command can take \"<literal>-d</literal>\" "
"option to create new directories and \"<literal>-P</literal>\" option to "
"prune empty directories."
msgstr ""
"La commande «&nbsp;<literal>cvs up</literal>&nbsp;» peut prendre l’option "
"«&nbsp;<literal>-d</literal>&nbsp;» pour créer de nouveaux répertoires et "
"l’option «&nbsp;<literal>-P</literal>&nbsp;» pour supprimer les répertoires "
"vides."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You can checkout only a sub directory of \"<literal>module1</literal>\" by "
"providing its name as \"<literal>cvs co module1/subdir</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez ne vérifier qu'un sous-répertoire de «&nbsp;<literal>module1</"
"literal>&nbsp;» en indiquant son nom comme, par exemple, «&nbsp;<literal>cvs "
"co module1/sous-répertoire</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
msgid ""
"Notable options for CVS commands (use as first argument(s) to "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>cvs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry>)"
msgstr ""
"Options importantes des commandes CVS (à utiliser comme premier(s)paramètre"
"(s) à <citerefentry><refentrytitle>cvs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
msgid "option"
msgstr "option"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "<literal>-n</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-n</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "dry run, no effect"
msgstr "simulation, pas d'effet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "<literal>-t</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-t</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "display messages showing steps of cvs activity"
msgstr "afficher les messages montrant les étapes des actions de cvs"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Latest files from CVS"
msgstr "Derniers fichiers venant du CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"To get the latest files from CVS, use \"<literal>tomorrow</literal>\" by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Pour obtenir les derniers fichiers du CVS, utilisez «&nbsp;"
"<literal>tomorrow</literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ex -D tomorrow module_name"
msgstr "$ cvs ex -D tomorrow nom_module"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Administration of CVS"
msgstr "Administration de CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Add module alias \"<literal>mx</literal>\" to a CVS project (local server) "
"by the following."
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez l’alias «&nbsp;<literal>mx</literal>&nbsp;» à un projet CVS (serveur "
"local) de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project\n"
"$ cvs co CVSROOT/modules\n"
"$ cd CVSROOT\n"
"$ echo \"mx -a module1\" &gt;&gt;modules\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Now mx is an alias for module1\"\n"
"$ cvs release -d ."
msgstr ""
"$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/projet\n"
"$ cvs co CVSROOT/modules\n"
"$ cd CVSROOT\n"
"$ echo \"mx -a module1\" &gt;&gt;modules\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"mx est maintenant un alias de module1\"\n"
"$ cvs release -d ."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Now, you can check out \"<literal>module1</literal>\" (alias: \"<literal>mx</"
"literal>\") from CVS to \"<literal>new</literal>\" directory by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez maintenant vérifier «&nbsp;<literal>module1</"
"literal>&nbsp;» (alias&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>mx</literal>&nbsp;») depuis le "
"CVS vers le répertoire «&nbsp;<literal>new</literal>&nbsp;» de la manière "
"suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs co -d new mx\n"
"$ cd new"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs co -d nouveau mx\n"
"$ cd nouveau"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><para>
msgid ""
"In order to perform above procedure, you should have appropriate file "
"permissions."
msgstr ""
"Afin de pouvoir effectuer la procédure précédente, vous devrez avoir les "
"permissions d'accès aux fichier appropriées."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Execution bit for CVS checkout"
msgstr "Bit d'exécution pour la vérification («&nbsp;checkout&nbsp;») du CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"When you checkout files from CVS, their execution permission bit is retained."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque vous vérifiez des fichiers du CVS, leur bit d'autorisation en "
"exécution est conservé."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Whenever you see execution permission problems in a checked out file, e.g. "
"\"<literal>filename</literal>\", change its permission in the corresponding "
"CVS repository by the following to fix it."
msgstr ""
"Si vous rencontrez des problèmes de droits d'exécution avec un fichier "
"récupéré, par exemple «&nbsp;<literal>nom_fichier</literal>&nbsp;», modifiez-"
"en les permissions dans le répertoire correspondant du dépôt CVS par ce qui "
"suit afin de corriger ce problème&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chmod ugo-x filename"
msgstr "# chmod ugo-x nom_de_fichier"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"Subversion is a <emphasis role=\"strong\">recent-generation</emphasis> "
"version control system replacing older CVS.  It has most of CVS's features "
"except tags and branches."
msgstr ""
"Subversion est un système de contrôle de version de <emphasis role=\"strong"
"\">génération récente</emphasis> qui remplace l’ancien CVS. Il en possède la "
"plupart des fonctionnalités à l’exception des étiquettes et des branches."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"You need to install <literal>subversion</literal>, <literal>libapache2-svn</"
"literal> and <literal>subversion-tools</literal> packages to set up a "
"Subversion server."
msgstr ""
"Vous devrez installer les paquets <literal>subversion</literal>, "
"<literal>libapache2-svn</literal> et <literal>subversion-tools</literal> "
"pour mettre en place un serveur Subversion."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Configuration of Subversion repository"
msgstr "Configuration du dépôt Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Currently, the <literal>subversion</literal> package does not set up a "
"repository, so one must set it up manually.  One possible location for a "
"repository is in \"<literal>/srv/svn/project</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Actuellement, le paquet <literal>subversion</literal> ne configure pas le "
"dépôt, on doit donc le faire manuellement. Un emplacement possible pour le "
"dépôt se trouve en «&nbsp;<literal>/srv/svn/projet</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Create a directory by the following."
msgstr "Créez un répertoire de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mkdir -p        /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# mkdir -p        /srv/svn/projet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Create the repository database by the following."
msgstr "Créez la base de données du dépôt comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# svnadmin create /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# svnadmin create /srv/svn/projet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Access to Subversion via Apache2 server"
msgstr "Accès à Subversion par l’intermédiaire d'un serveur Apache2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"If you only access Subversion repository via Apache2 server, you just need "
"to make the repository only writable by the WWW server by the following."
msgstr ""
"Si vous n'avez accès au dépôt de Subversion que par un serveur Apache2, il "
"vous suffira de ne rendre le dépôt accessible en écriture que par le serveur "
"WWW de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/svn/projet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Add (or uncomment) the following in \"<literal>/etc/apache2/mods-available/"
"dav_svn.conf</literal>\" to allow access to the repository via user "
"authentication."
msgstr ""
"Ajouter (ou décommenter) ce qui suit dans «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/apache2/mods-"
"available/dav_svn.conf</literal>&nbsp;» afin de permettre l’accès au dépôt "
"avec une authentification de l’utilisateur."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;Location /project&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /srv/svn/project\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Subversion repository\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"&lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"    Require valid-user\n"
"&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;Location /projet&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /srv/svn/projet\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Dépôt subversion\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"&lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"    Require valid-user\n"
"&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Create a user authentication file with the command by the following."
msgstr ""
"Créer un fichier d'authentification des utilisateurs avec la commande "
"suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# htpasswd2 -c /etc/subversion/passwd some-username"
msgstr "# htpasswd2 -c /etc/subversion/passwd nom_utilisateur"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Restart Apache2."
msgstr "Redémarrez Apache2."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Your new Subversion repository is accessible at URL \"<literal>http://"
"localhost/project</literal>\" and \"<literal>http://example.com/project</"
"literal>\" from <citerefentry><refentrytitle>svn</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> (assuming your URL of "
"web server is \"<literal>http://example.com/</literal>\")."
msgstr ""
"Votre nouveau dépôt Subversion est accessible à l’URL «&nbsp;<literal>http://"
"localhost/projet</literal>&nbsp;» et «&nbsp;<literal>http://example.com/"
"projet</literal>&nbsp;» depuis <citerefentry><refentrytitle>svn</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> (en supposant que "
"l’URL du serveur web est «&nbsp;<literal>http://example.com/</"
"literal>&nbsp;»)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Local access to Subversion by group"
msgstr "Accès local à Subversion par un groupe"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"The following sets up Subversion repository for the local access by a group, "
"e.g. <literal>project</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Ce qui suit configure le dépôt Subversion pour un accès local par un groupe, "
"<literal>projet</literal>, par exemple&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# chmod  2775     /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chown -R root:src /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   /srv/svn/project"
msgstr ""
"# chmod  2775     /srv/svn/projet\n"
"# chown -R root:src /srv/svn/projet\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   /srv/svn/projet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Your new Subversion repository is group accessible at URL \"<literal>file:///"
"localhost/srv/svn/project</literal>\" or \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</"
"literal>\" from <citerefentry><refentrytitle>svn</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> for local users "
"belonging to <literal>project</literal> group.  You must run commands, such "
"as <literal>svn</literal>, <literal>svnserve</literal>, <literal>svnlook</"
"literal>, and <literal>svnadmin</literal> under \"<literal>umask 002</"
"literal>\" to ensure group access."
msgstr ""
"Votre nouveau dépôt Subversion est accessible aux utilisateurs locaux "
"appartenant au groupe <literal>projet</literal>à l’URL «&nbsp;"
"<literal>file:///localhost/srv/svn/projet</literal>&nbsp;» ou «&nbsp;"
"<literal>file:///srv/svn/projet</literal>&nbsp;» depuis "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>svn</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> . Vous devrez lancer des commandes comme <literal>svn</"
"literal>, <literal>svnserve</literal>, <literal>svnlook</literal> et "
"<literal>svnadmin</literal> avec «&nbsp;<literal>umask 002</literal>&nbsp;» "
"afin de permettre l’accès au groupe."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Remote access to Subversion via SSH"
msgstr "Accès distant à Subversion avec SSH"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"A group accessible Subversion repository is at URL \"<literal>example.com:/"
"srv/svn/project</literal>\" for SSH, you can access it from "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>svn</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> at URL \"<literal>svn+ssh://example.com:/srv/svn/project</"
"literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Un dépôt Subversion accessible à un groupe se trouve pour SSH à l’URL «&nbsp;"
"<literal>example.com:/srv/svn/projet</literal>&nbsp;», vous pouvez y accéder "
"avec <citerefentry><refentrytitle>svn</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> à l’URL «&nbsp;<literal>svn+ssh://example.com:/srv/"
"svn/projet</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Subversion directory structure"
msgstr "Structure de répertoires de Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Many projects uses directory tree similar to the following for Subversion to "
"compensate its lack of branches and tags."
msgstr ""
"Afin de compenser le manque de branches et d'étiquettes, de nombreux projets "
"utilisent une arborescence de répertoires semblable à la suivante pour "
"Subversion&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  ----- module1\n"
"    |   |-- branches\n"
"    |   |-- tags\n"
"    |   |   |-- release-1.0\n"
"    |   |   `-- release-2.0\n"
"    |   |\n"
"    |   `-- trunk\n"
"    |       |-- file1\n"
"    |       |-- file2\n"
"    |       `-- file3\n"
"    |\n"
"    `-- module2"
msgstr ""
"  ----- module1\n"
"    |   |-- branches\n"
"    |   |-- tags\n"
"    |   |   |-- version-1.0\n"
"    |   |   `-- version-2.0\n"
"    |   |\n"
"    |   `-- trunk\n"
"    |       |-- fichier1\n"
"    |       |-- fichier2\n"
"    |       `-- fichier3\n"
"    |\n"
"    `-- module2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You must use \"<literal>svn copy …</literal>\" command to mark branches and "
"tags.  This ensures Subversion to record modification history of files "
"properly and saves storage spaces."
msgstr ""
"Vous devez utiliser la commande «&nbsp;<literal>svn copy …</literal>&nbsp;» "
"pour marquer les branches et les étiquettes. Cela permet de s'assurer que "
"Subversion enregistre correctement l’historique de modification des fichiers "
"et économise l’espace disque."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Importing a new source to Subversion"
msgstr "Importer une nouvelle source vers Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Import it to Subversion with the following parameters."
msgstr "Importez-le dans Subversion avec les paramètres suivants&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Subversion site URL: \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"URL du site Subversion&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>file:///srv/svn/projet</"
"literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Subversion directory: \"<literal>module1/trunk</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"Répertoire de Subversion&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>module1/trunk</"
"literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
msgid "Subversion tag: \"<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"Étiquette de Subversion&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>module1/tags/Version-"
"initiale</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to/module1\n"
"$ svn import file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk -m \"Start module1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-initial"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/chemin/vers/module1\n"
"$ svn import file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk -m \"Lancement module1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/tags/Version-initiale"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Alternatively, by the following."
msgstr "Ou encore, comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn import ~/path/to/module1 file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk -m \"Start module1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-initial"
msgstr ""
"$ svn import ~/chemin/vers/module1 file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk -m \"Lancement module1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/tags/Version-initiale"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You can replace URLs such as \"<literal>file:///…</literal>\" by any other "
"URL formats such as \"<literal>http://…</literal>\" and \"<literal>svn+ssh://"
"…</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez remplacer des formats d'URL comme «&nbsp;<literal>file:///…</"
"literal>&nbsp;» par d'autres formats d'URL comme «&nbsp;<literal> http://…</"
"literal>&nbsp;» et «&nbsp;<literal>svn+ssh://…</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Work flow of Subversion"
msgstr "Flux de travail avec Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Here is an example of typical work flow using Subversion with its native "
"client."
msgstr ""
"Voici un exemple typique de flux de travail utilisant Subversion avec son "
"client natif."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"Client commands offered by the <literal>git-svn</literal> package may offer "
"alternative work flow of Subversion using the <literal>git</literal> "
"command.  See <xref linkend=\"_git_for_the_subversion_repository\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Les commandes du client proposées par le paquet <literal>git-svn</literal> "
"peuvent proposer un mode d’utilisation de remplacement pour Subversion en "
"utilisant la commande <literal>git</literal>. Consultez <xref linkend="
"\"_git_for_the_subversion_repository\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Check all available modules from Subversion project pointed by URL "
"\"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Vérifiez de la manière suivante tous les modules disponibles depuis le "
"projet pointé par l’URL «&nbsp;<literal>file:///srv/svn/projet</"
"literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn list file:///srv/svn/project\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ svn list file:///srv/svn/projet\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Checkout \"<literal>module1/trunk</literal>\" to a directory "
"\"<literal>module1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr ""
"Récupérez «&nbsp;<literal>module1/trunk</literal>&nbsp;» dans un répertoire "
"«&nbsp;<literal>module1</literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk module1\n"
"$ cd module1"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/chemin/vers\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk module1\n"
"$ cd module1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn diff"
msgstr "$ svn diff"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Overwrite \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" file with the clean copy from "
"Subversion by the following."
msgstr ""
"Écrasez le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>fichier_a_annuler</literal>&nbsp;» avec "
"une nouvelle copie propre depuis Subversion comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn revert file_to_undo"
msgstr "$ svn revert fichier_a_annuler"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Save the updated local source tree to Subversion by the following."
msgstr ""
"Enregistrez l’arbre local des sources mis à jour vers Subversion comme "
"suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"Describe change\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"Décrire les modifications\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create and add \"<literal>file_to_add</literal>\" file to Subversion by the "
"following."
msgstr ""
"Créez et ajoutez le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>fichier_a_ajouter</"
"literal>&nbsp;» dans Subversion comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ vi file_to_add\n"
"$ svn add file_to_add\n"
"$ svn ci -m \"Added file_to_add\""
msgstr ""
"$ vi fichier_a_ajouter\n"
"$ svn add fichier_a_ajouter\n"
"$ svn ci -m \"fichier_a_ajouter ajouté\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Merge the latest version from Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Fusionnez la dernière version depuis Subversion comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn up"
msgstr "$ svn up"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Look for unmodified code in, e.g., \"<literal>filename.r6</literal>\", "
"\"<literal>filename.r9</literal>\", and \"<literal>filename.mine</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Recherchez le code non modifié, par exemple «&nbsp;<literal>nom_fichier.r6</"
"literal>&nbsp;», «&nbsp;<literal>nom_fichier.r9</literal>&nbsp;» et «&nbsp;"
"<literal>nom_fichier.mien</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn ci -m \"last commit for Release-1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-1"
msgstr ""
"$ svn ci -m \"dernier «&nbsp;commit&nbsp;» pour la Release-1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/tags/Release-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn rm file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-1"
msgstr "$ svn rm file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/tags/Release-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Check in changes to Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Récupérez les modifications depuis Subversion comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"real last commit for Release-1\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"vraiment le dernier commit pour Release-1\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Re-add the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" from updated "
"Subversion HEAD of trunk by the following."
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez de nouveau la balise «&nbsp;<literal>Version-1</literal>&nbsp;» "
"depuis la version mise à jour de HEAD de trunk de Subversion comme "
"suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-1"
msgstr "$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/tags/Version-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Create a branch with a path \"<literal>module1/branches/Release-initial-"
"bugfixes</literal>\" from the original version pointed by the path "
"\"<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>\" and check it out to "
"\"<literal>~/path/to/old</literal>\" directory by the following."
msgstr ""
"Créez une branche dont le chemin est «&nbsp;<literal>module1/branches/"
"Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>&nbsp;» depuis la version initiale pointée "
"par le chemin «&nbsp;<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>&nbsp;» "
"et récupérez-le vers le répertoire «&nbsp;<literal>~/chemin/vers/ancien</"
"literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-initial file:///srv/svn/project/module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes\n"
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/project/module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes old\n"
"$ cd old"
msgstr ""
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/tags/Version-initiale file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/branches/Version-initale-corrections-de-bogues\n"
"$ cd ~/chemin/vers\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/branches/Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues ancien\n"
"$ cd ancien"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"Use \"<literal>module1/trunk@{2005-12-20}</literal>\" (<ulink url=\"&isoigab;"
"\">ISO 8601</ulink> date format) instead of \"<literal>module1/tags/Release-"
"initial</literal>\" to specify particular date as the branch point."
msgstr ""
"Utilisez «&nbsp;<literal>module1/trunk@{2005-12-20}</literal>&nbsp;» (format "
"de date <ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink>) plutôt que «&nbsp;"
"<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>&nbsp;» pour indiquer une "
"date particulière comme point de branche."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Work on this local source tree pointing to branch \"<literal>Release-initial-"
"bugfixes</literal>\" which is based on the original version."
msgstr ""
"Travaillez sur cet arbre de sources local pointant vers la branche «&nbsp;"
"<literal>Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues</literal>&nbsp;» qui est "
"basée sur la version initiale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Sync with files modified by others on this branch by the following."
msgstr ""
"Effectuez la synchronisation avec les fichiers de cette branche modifiés par "
"d'autres comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"checked into this branch\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"récupérés dans cette branche\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Update the local tree with HEAD of trunk by the following."
msgstr ""
"Mettez à jour l’arborescence local avec HEAD de trunk de la manière "
"suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn switch file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk"
msgstr "$ svn switch file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/trunk"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Update the local tree (content = HEAD of trunk) by merging from the "
"\"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch by the following."
msgstr ""
"Mettez à jour l’arborescence locale (contenu = HEAD de trunk) en fusionnant "
"depuis la branche «&nbsp;<literal>Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues</"
"literal>&nbsp;» par ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn merge file:///srv/svn/project/module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes"
msgstr "$ svn merge file:///srv/svn/projet/module1/branches/Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"merged Release-initial-bugfixes\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"Version-initiale-corrections-de-bogues fusionnée\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"You can checkout only a sub directory of \"<literal>module1</literal>\" by "
