#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
msgid ""
"Debug is important part of programing activities.  Knowing how to debug "
"programs makes you a good Debian user who can produce meaningful bug reports."
msgstr ""
"Le débogage est une partie de l’activité de programmations. Savoir comme "
"déboguer des programmes fera de vous un bon utilisateur de Debian qui pourra "
"produire des rapports de bogues documentés."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Basic gdb execution"
msgstr "Exécution de base de gdb"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Primary <ulink url=\"&debugger;\">debugger</ulink> on Debian is "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry> which enables you to inspect a program while it executes."
msgstr ""
"Le <ulink url=\"&debugger;\">debogueur</ulink> primaire sous Debian est "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></"
"citerefentry>, il vous permet d'inspecter un programme alors qu'il tourne."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Let's install <literal>gdb</literal> and related programs by the following."
msgstr ""
"Installons <literal>gdb</literal> et les programmes associés par ce qui  "
"suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt-get install gdb gdb-doc build-essential devscripts"
msgstr "# apt-get install gdb gdb-doc build-essential devscripts"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Good tutorial of <literal>gdb</literal> is provided by \"<literal>info gdb</"
"literal>\" or found <ulink url=\"&elsewhereontheweb;\">elsewhere on the web</"
"ulink>.  Here is a simple example of using <citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> on a "
"\"<literal>program</literal>\" compiled with the \"<literal>-g</literal>\" "
"option to produce debugging information."
msgstr ""
"Un bon didacticiel de <literal>gdb</literal> est proposé par «&nbsp;"
"<literal>info gdb</literal>&nbsp;«» ou peut être trouvé <ulink url="
"\"&elsewhereontheweb;\">ailleurs sur le web</ulink>. Voici un exemple simple "
"d'utilisation de <citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> sur un «&nbsp;"
"<literal>program</literal>&nbsp;» compilé avec l’option «&nbsp;<literal>-g</"
"literal>&nbsp;» qui produit les informations de débogage."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ gdb program\n"
"(gdb) b 1                # set break point at line 1\n"
"(gdb) run args           # run program with args\n"
"(gdb) next               # next line\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) step               # step forward\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm             # print parm\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm=12          # set value to 12\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) quit"
msgstr ""
"$ gdb program\n"
"(gdb) b 1                # définit un point d'arrêt à la ligne 1\n"
"(gdb) run args           # lancer les programmes avec des paramètres \n"
"(gdb) next               # ligne suivante\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) step               # avancer d'un pas\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm             # afficher parm\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm=12          # définir sa valeur à 12\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) quit"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
msgid ""
"Many <citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry> commands can be abbreviated.  Tab expansion works "
"as in the shell."
msgstr ""
"De nombreuses commandes de <citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> possèdent une "
"abréviation. L’expansion à l’aide de la touche de tabulation fonctionne "
"comme avec l’interpréteur de commandes."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
msgid "Debugging the Debian package"
msgstr "Déboguer un paquet Debian"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"Since all installed binaries should be stripped on the Debian system by "
"default, most debugging symbols are removed in the normal package.  In order "
"to debug Debian packages with <citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>, corresponding "
"<literal>*-dbg</literal> packages need to be installed (e.g. <literal>libc6-"
"dbg</literal> in the case of <literal>libc6</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Comme, par défaut, sous Debian, tous les paquets binaires sont «&nbsp;"
"strippés&nbsp;» (dépouillés de leurs symboles de débogage), la plupart des "
"symboles de débogage sont supprimés des paquets normaux. Pour pouvoir "
"déboguer des paquets Debian à l’aide de <citerefentry><refentrytitle>gdb</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>, les paquets "
"<literal>*-dbg</literal> correspondants doivent être installés (par exemple "
"<literal>libc6-dbg</literal> dans le cas de <literal>libc6</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid ""
"If a package to be debugged does not provide its <literal>*-dbg</literal> "
"package, you need to install it after rebuilding it by the following."
msgstr ""
"Si un paquet à déboguer ne possède pas de paquet <literal>*-dbg</literal> "
"correspondant, vous devrez l’installer après l’avoir reconstruit comme "
"suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ mkdir /path/new ; cd /path/new\n"
"$ sudo apt-get update\n"
"$ sudo apt-get dist-upgrade\n"
"$ sudo apt-get install fakeroot devscripts build-essential\n"
"$ sudo apt-get build-dep source_package_name\n"
"$ apt-get source package_name\n"
"$ cd package_name*"
msgstr ""
"$ mkdir /chemin/nouveau ; cd /chemin/nouveau\n"
"$ sudo apt-get update\n"
"$ sudo apt-get dist-upgrade\n"
"$ sudo apt-get install fakeroot devscripts build-essential\n"
"$ sudo apt-get build-dep nom_paquet_source\n"
"$ apt-get source nom_paquet\n"
"$ cd nom_paquet*"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
msgid "Fix bugs if needed."
